-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Using the same guitar that School of Seven Bells played their (poorly eq&#039;d) set with, Prefuse 73, coming south from Portland the evening before, using an MPC 2500 and various other controlling hardware, gave the "all ages" crowd at Slim&#039;s (http://www.slims-sf.com) just exactly what they came for: SHADOWY, NON-STOP HIP-HOP BEATS FLAVORED WITH DARK & GLITCHY ELECTRONIC NUANCES, ALONG WITH DISTORTED GUITAR RIFFS AND A LIVE DRUMMER TO BOOT!!!
